text: Gangoh is a town and a municipal board in Saharanpur district in the state of Uttar Pradesh, India. ==Demographics== India census, Gangoh had a population of 59,279. Males constitute 52.83% of the population and females 47.16%. Gangoh has an average literacy rate of 63.51%, lower than the national average of 74.04%. ==History== The Dargah Sharif of the great Sufi saints Mamu Allah Bakhsh and Mata Lado Rani According to the 1911 British publication The Imperial Gazetteer of India: there are 25 mohalle in gangoh. and famous temples of Gangoh are baba Haridas ji Maharaj, Sanatan Dharma Sabha popularly known as Sabha, Bala ji dham and vaishnodevi temple". == Notable people == * Abdul Quddus Gangohi * Rashid Ahmad Gangohi * Pradeep Kumar, Indian politician and Member of Parliament ==References== ==External links== * Gangoh in Imperial Gazetteer of India, 1909 Category:Cities and towns in Saharanpur district
